		<body>
			<div type="transcription">
				<div type="original" xml:lang="en">
					<p>51 <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2781194/burgenland.html">BURGENLAND</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">JEWS</term> MARRONED ON BREAKWATER IN <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/791630/danube-river.html">DANUBE</placeName>: 35 REPATRIATED AND ARRESTED BY NAZI. 15 STILL HIDING IN WOOD ON
						FRONTIER.</p>
					<p><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName>, <date when="1938-04-20">Apr. 20th</date>. (<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-005433">Jewish Telegraphic agency</orgName>).</p>
					<p>Fifty-one <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2781194/burgenland.html">Burgenland</placeName> were rescued on Sunday night from a breakwater in the <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/791630/danube-river.html">Danube</placeName> after the inhabitants of the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czech</placeName> town of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3077172/devin.html"
							>Theben</placeName> had been attracted by their cries of distress. The breakwater was about 100 meters from the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czech</placeName> side of the river. <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czech</placeName> frontier guards brought the marooned <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3077172/devin.html"
							>Theben</placeName>.</p>
					<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term>, who are from the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Austrian</placeName> frontier towns of <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/2774348/kittsee.html">Kittsee</placeName> and <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3059704/jarovce.html">Kroatisch-Jarendorf</placeName>, declared that they had been arrested by <orgName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-358">Nazi stormtroopers</orgName> who had confiscated their <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-887" type="subject">property</term>, put them in a motor-boat and left them marooned on the
						breakwater.</p>
					<p>Among the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> was the 82-year-old <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-735" type="subject">Rabbi</term> of <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/2774348/kittsee.html">Kittsee</placeName>, <persName ref="#ehri_bf_perls_armin">Perls</persName>, <note>im Originaltext fälschlich: <persName>Parls</persName></note> his <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292"
							type="subject">sick</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">wife</term>, and many <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> and small <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824"
							type="subject">children</term>.</p>
					<p>The <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3077172/devin.html">Theben</placeName> innkeeper <persName ref="#ehri_bf_sieber">Sieber</persName> took pity on the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> and put them up at his
						inn. They were later fetched by <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czecho-Slovak</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">police</term> who took them to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">police</term> detention station in <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/3060972/bratislava.html">Bratislava</placeName>. Only the <persName ref="#ehri_bf_perls_ema">wife of Rabbi Perls</persName> was permitted to stay in the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-870" type="subject">Jewish
							hospital</term> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3060972/bratislava.html">Bratislava</placeName>, the rest were taken across the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/719819/hungary.html">Hungarian</placeName> frontier.</p>
					<p>The <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czecho-Slovak</placeName> authorities declare that they cannot allow any <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-101" type="subject">Jewish refugees</term> from <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Austria</placeName> to stay in the country, because, if they do, the Nazis would deport all the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2781194/burgenland.html">Burgenland</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czecho-Slovakia</placeName>.</p>
					<p>The <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/719819/hungary.html">Hungarian</placeName> authorities deported the 51 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jews</term> to <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Austria</placeName> on Tuesday. 35 of them crossed the border into <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Austria</placeName> and were arrested by <orgName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-358">Nazi stormtroopers</orgName> of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2774348/kittsee.html">Kittsee</placeName> who imprisoned them in one of their barracks. The remaining 15 <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-101" type="subject">refugees</term> were yesterday still in the Pheasants’ Wood along the border of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Austria</placeName>.</p>
					<p>A <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Jewish</term> delegation left <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3060972/bratislava.html">Bratislava</placeName> for <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html"
							>Prague</placeName> to ask the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czecho-Slovak</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1110" type="subject">Minister</term> of the Interior, Dr. <persName ref="#ehri_bf_cerny_josef">Czerny</persName>, to allow the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-101" type="subject"
							>Jewish refugees</term> to stay in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czecho-Slovakia</placeName>. Another delegation is to leave for <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2643743/london.html">London</placeName> to lodge a formal
						protest with the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2635167/united-kingdom-of-great-britain-and-northern-ireland.html">British</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">Government</term> against such mass expulsions.</p>
				</div>
				<div type="translation" xml:lang="cs">
					<p>51 <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2781194/burgenland.html">BURGENLANDSKÝCH</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">ŽIDŮ</term> UVÍZLO NA VLNOLAMU NA <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/791630/danube-river.html">DUNAJI</placeName>: 35 REPATRIOVÁNO A ZATČENO NACISTY. 15 SE STÁLE SKRÝVÁ V LESÍCH NA
						HRANICI.</p>
					<p><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Praha</placeName>, 20. dubna. (<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-005433">Jewish Telegraphic agency</orgName>).</p>
					<p>Padesát jedna <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Židů</term> z <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2781194/burgenland.html">Burgenlandu</placeName> bylo v neděli v noci zachráněno z vlnolamu na <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/791630/danube-river.html">Dunaji</placeName> poté, co obyvatelé <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">československého</placeName> města <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3077172/devin.html"
							>Děvín</placeName> zaslechli jejich volání o pomoc. Vlnolam je asi 100 metrů daleko od <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">československé</placeName> strany řeky. <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html"
							>Českoslovenští</placeName> pohraničníci odvedli uvízlé <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Židy</term> do <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3077172/devin.html">Děvína</placeName>.</p>
					<p><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Židé</term>, původně z <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">rakouských</placeName> pohraničních měst <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/2774348/kittsee.html">Kittsee</placeName> a <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3059704/jarovce.html">Jarovce</placeName>, uvedli, že byli zatčeni příslušníky nacistických úderných oddílů, kteří zkonfiskovali jejich <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-887#majetek" type="subject">majetek</term>, pak je posadili do motorového člunu a následně je ponechali svému osudu na vlnolamu.</p>
					<p>Mezi těmito <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Židy</term> byl i 82letý <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-735" type="subject">rabín</term> z <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2774348/kittsee.html"
							>Kittsee</placeName>, <persName ref="#ehri_bf_perls_armin">Perls</persName><note type="gloss">V původním textu uvedeno špatně: Parls.</note>,jeho <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">nemocná</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">manželka</term> a mnoho <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">žen</term> a malých <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824"
							type="subject">dětí</term>.</p>
					<p>Majitel hostince v <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3077172/devin.html">Děvíně</placeName>
						<persName ref="#ehri_bf_sieber">Sieber</persName> se nad <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Židy</term> slitoval a ubytoval je ve svém hostinci. Později byli odvedeni <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">československou</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">policií</term> do <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">policejní</term> cely předběžného zadržení v <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/3060972/bratislava.html">Bratislavě</placeName>. Pouze <persName ref="#ehri_bf_perls_ema">manželce rabína Perlse</persName> bylo povoleno zůstat v <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-870" type="subject">Židovské
							nemocnici</term> v <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3060972/bratislava.html">Bratislavě</placeName>, ostatní byli odvedeni za <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/719819/hungary.html">maďarské</placeName> hranice.</p>
					<p><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Československá</placeName> oficiální místa uvádějí, že nemohou povolit pobyt žádných <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-101" type="subject">židovských uprchlíků</term> z <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Rakouska</placeName> v republice, protože – pokud by tak učinila – by pak nacisté přistoupili k deportaci všech <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2781194/burgenland.html">burgenlandských</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Židů</term> do <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Československa</placeName>.</p>
					<p><placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/719819/hungary.html">Maďarské</placeName> orgány deportovaly 51 zachráněných <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject">Židů</term> do <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Rakouska</placeName> v úterý. 35 z nich překročilo hranice s <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Rakouskem</placeName> a bylo zatčeno <orgName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-358">příslušníky nacistických úderných oddílů</orgName> z <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2774348/kittsee.html">Kittsee</placeName>, jimiž pak byli uvězněni v jedné z jejich kasárenských budov. Zbývajících 15
							<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-101" type="subject">uprchlíků</term> se během včerejška stále skrývalo v Jarovské bažantnici u hranic s <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2782113/republic-of-austria.html">Rakouskem</placeName>.</p>
					<p>Do <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prahy</placeName> se z <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3060972/bratislava.html">Bratislavy</placeName> vydala <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864" type="subject"
							>židovská</term> delegace, aby požádala <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">československého</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1110" type="subject">ministra</term> vnitra, Dr. <persName ref="#ehri_bf_cerny_josef">Černého</persName>, aby umožnil <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-101" type="subject">židovským
							uprchlíkům</term> zůstat v <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Československu</placeName>. V nejbližších dnech bude vyslána další delegace do <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2643743/london.html">Londýna</placeName>, aby u
							<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2635167/united-kingdom-of-great-britain-and-northern-ireland.html">britské</placeName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">vlády</term> podala formální protest proti těmto případům hromadného vyhánění.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
